50|$|In 2002, at the World Food Summit in June, the FAO {{adopted the}} Declaration of the World Food Summit: {{five years later}} calling for the {{establishment}} of an intergovernmental working group to prepare a set of guidelines on the implementation of the right to food. In November, the <b>FAO</b> <b>Council</b> set up an Intergovernmental Working Group which drafts the Right to Food Guidelines.|$|E
50|$|The World Summit on Food Security {{took place}} in Rome, Italy, between 16 and 18 November 2009. The {{decision}} to convene the summit {{was taken by the}} <b>FAO</b> <b>Council,</b> at the proposal of FAO Director-General Jacques Diouf. Sixty Heads of State and Government attended the summit. Countries unanimously adopted a declaration pledging renewed commitment to eradicate hunger from the earth at the earliest possible date.|$|E
